      <p>BrAPI client code libraries have been created in several languages, such as Java (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/imilne/jhi-brapi">https://github.com/imilne/jhi-brapi</ext-link>), the BrAPI R package (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/CIP-RIU/brapi">https://github.com/CIP-RIU/brapi</ext-link>), Brapi Drupal for PHP, and brapi.js for Javascript (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/solgenomics/BrAPI-js">https://github.com/solgenomics/BrAPI-js</ext-link>). A non-exhaustive list of current client applications is given in <xref rid="btz190-T3" ref-type="table">Table 3</xref>. It is possible for service providers to use BrAPI for the implementation of native website features. Some of these features have been implemented as reusable BrAPI compliant widgets, which we call BrAPI Apps or ‘BrAPPs’ for short. The available BrAPPs are listed on the BrAPI website (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://brapi.org/brapps.php">https://brapi.org/brapps.php</ext-link>). <xref ref-type="fig" rid="btz190-F2">Figure 2</xref> shows a screenshot of an example BrAPP which performs graphical filtering of phenotypic values.
</p>
